#ROOM
Vnum     25517
Name     &GThe Rolling Hills&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The flat savanna begins to pitch and roll into gentle hills as you travel
further north. In the distance, you catch your first glimpse of the
breathtaking, towering mesas of Thunder Bluff.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    25512
Desc      The northern plains.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    25516
Desc      Thunderhorn Water Well.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    25519
Desc      The northern foothills.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    25518
Desc      Wildmane Water Well.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25518
Name     &GWildmane Water Well&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     Another vital water source for the plains, though this one is dangerously
close to the harpy hunting grounds to the north. Travelers fill their
skins quickly and keep an eye on the sky.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    25517
Desc      The rolling hills.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25519
Name     &GThe Northern Foothills&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The grass becomes sparse, and the wind picks up significantly. The shadows
of enormous mesas stretch across the land. The screech of harpies echoes
from the cliffs to the west.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    25517
Desc      The rolling hills.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    25520
Desc      The Harpy Roost.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    25524
Desc      The path to the great city.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25520
Name     &CThe Harpy Roost&d~
Sector   hills~
Desc     The cliffs here are covered in crude nests made of stolen goods and bones.
Vicious Windfury Harpies dive from the high rocks, attacking anyone who
trespasses in their territory with razor-sharp talons and wind magic.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    25519
Desc      The northern foothills.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 25509 3 25520
  Reset G 1 25507 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25521
Name     &GThe Golden Plains - West&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A wide, empty expanse of plains on the western edge of Mulgore. The
wind blows undisturbed for miles. It is a quiet, contemplative place.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    25508
Desc      The central plains.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    25522
Desc      The Kodo Graveyard.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25522
Name     &dThe Kodo Graveyard&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A solemn, quiet valley filled with the massive, bleached bones of ancient
Kodo Beasts who have come here to die. The Tauren consider this a sacred,
protected site.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    25521
Desc      The western plains.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25523
Name     &GGhost Walker Post&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A small, isolated Tauren outpost situated perfectly to watch the paths
leading out of Mulgore and into the Barrens or Desolace. A few braves
rest here by a small fire.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    25524
Desc      The path to Thunder Bluff.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25524
Name     &GPath to Thunder Bluff&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The dirt path is incredibly wide here, trampled down by countless hooves
and paws over generations. Directly ahead, the awe-inspiring capital of
the Tauren rises impossibly high into the sky on a massive pillar of stone.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    25519
Desc      The northern foothills.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    25523
Desc      Ghost Walker Post.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    25525
Desc      The base of the Great Lift.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25525
Name     &GBase of the Great Lift&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You stand at the bottom of a truly massive mesa. Towering wooden scaffolding
and immense ropes stretch all the way to the top, where the city rests.
Two large wooden platforms serve as elevators to the summit.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    25524
Desc      The path back to the plains.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    25526
Desc      Step onto the elevator.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 25503 2 25525
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25526
Name     &GThe Great Lift - Ascending&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The massive wooden platform shudders and groans as an immense counter-weight
system pulls it upward. The golden plains of Mulgore shrink below you,
revealing the breathtaking scale of the zone.
~
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    25525
Desc      The base of the lift.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction up~
ToRoom    25527
Desc      The top of the lift.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25527
Name     &GThe Great Lift - Top&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The elevator grinds to a halt at the summit of the mesa. You step off
onto a high wooden platform. The wind up here is incredibly strong and
pure. To the north lies the entrance to the great city.
~
#EXIT
Direction down~
ToRoom    25526
Desc      The descending lift.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    25528
Desc      A rope bridge.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25528
Name     &GThunder Bluff - Entrance Bridge&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A dizzyingly high rope and wood bridge connects the lift platform to the
main mesa of the city. Totems rattle in the wind, and braves patrol the
span tirelessly.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    25527
Desc      The Great Lift.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    25529
Desc      The Totem Poles.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     25529
Name     &GThunder Bluff - The Totem Poles&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     You have reached the edge of the great capital. Massive, intricately
carved, and brightly painted totems welcome you. From here, you can step
forward into the Central Mesa and explore the legendary home of the
Bloodhoof tribe.
~
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    25528
Desc      The entrance bridge.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    15000
Desc      Enter the Central Mesa of Thunder Bluff.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ENDAREA
